<HEADLINE>
Urgent Moscow Asks Atlantic Organization for Help in Rescuing Crew on
Board Sunken Submarine
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Washington <TIMEX2 val="2000-08-15" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">8-15</TIMEX2> (AFP) -

Officials at the Pentagon said <TIMEX2 val="2000-08-15" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">today</TIMEX2> <TIMEX2 val="2000-08-15" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">Tuesday</TIMEX2> that Russia has asked
the North Atlantic Treaty Organization for help in rescuing the crew
members on board the Russian submarine, Kursk, lying at the bottom of
the Barents Sea.
</TEXT>
